%N A395018 Decimal expansion of the mode of the distribution of distances between two points in the interior of a unit cube.
%C A395018 The second of the 4 roots of 5*x^4 - 32*x^3 + 18*Pi*x^2 - 8*Pi*x = 0.
%H A395018 Arak M. Mathai, Peter Moschopoulos, and Giorgio Pederzoli, <a href="https://rivista-statistica.unibo.it/article/view/1104">Distance between random points in a cube</a>, Statistica, Vol. 59, No. 1 (1999), pp. 61-81; <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/268489321">ResearchGate link</a>.
%H A395018 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/CubeLinePicking.html">Cube Line Picking</a>.		
%H A395018 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%e A395018 0.675230751991264244633196900774754334312565525608912...
%t A395018 RealDigits[x /. FindRoot[5*x^4 - 32*x^3 + 18*Pi*x^2 - 8*Pi*x, {x, 1/2}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]][[1]]
%o A395018 (PARI) solve(x = 1/2, 1, 5*x^4 - 32*x^3 + 18*Pi*x^2 - 8*Pi*x)
%Y A395018 Cf. A073012 (mean), A395017 (median), A394605 (disk), A394607 (square), A395019 (ball), A395016.
